methods.closeSession:
Reduces the liveness of the session.

:param session: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState) - the session to close
methods.getCurrentSession:
Lookup a session via the SessionServiceGrpcImpl.SESSION_CONTEXT_KEY. This method is only valid in the context of
 the original calling gRPC thread.

:return: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState) the session attached to this gRPC request
methods.getExpirationDelayMs: :return: (long) the configured token duration in milliseconds
methods.getOptionalSession:
Lookup a session via the SessionServiceGrpcImpl.SESSION_CONTEXT_KEY. This method is only valid in the context of
 the original calling gRPC thread.

:return: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState) the session attached to this gRPC request; null if no session is established
methods.getSessionForToken:
Lookup a session by token.

:param token: (java.util.UUID) - the session secret to look for
:return: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState) the session
methods.newSession:
Create a new session object for the provided auth context.

:param authContext: (io.deephaven.util.auth.AuthContext) - the auth context of the session
:return: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState) a new session independent of all other existing sessions
methods.refreshToken:
If enough time has passed since the last token refresh, rotate to a new token and reset the expiration deadline.

:param session: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionState) - the session to refresh
:return: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.session.SessionService.TokenExpiration) the most recent token expiration
